Telefonica Czech Unit Retreats Second Day After S&P Rating Cut

-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 
2011-08-12T10:01:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-12/telefonica-czech-unit-retreats-second-day-after-s-p-rating-cut.html
Telefonica Czech Republic AS dropped
for a second day after  Standard & Poor’s  downgraded the largest
Czech phone operator’s credit rating to BBB+ from A- yesterday.  The unit of Spain’s Telefonica SA fell as much as 1.6
percent and traded down 0.7 percent to 402 koruna as of 11:34
a.m. in Prague. The stock was the second-worst performer in the
PX gauge of companies, which rose 1 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
 kchamonikola@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at   gserkin@bloomberg.net  